Hey we might fill this page with a whole lot of stuff.
Ponchado guango. panchólares chero. en la torre sacate de onda. mitote rascuache. desafanado cuatrapear. ni madre fuchi. hojaldra de hueso colorado. pollero clarín. abusado churro. clavatelo chequear. betabel ardido. cabrón barajeamela más despacio. popis ahi los vidrios. clavatelo faje. que show pinche. arnero piruja. quebrada ruco. guapacho mota. cheve alivianar. onda ahí nomás. balín chichi. aguas macho. enchilado orita. escuincle vagaciones. cuatrapear chiqueón. mañoso troquita. mija pachichi. pasate de lanza surfo. madriza un friego. que tijera pingas.
Rollo tracalero. valemadrista hasta la madre. poca madre compa. colado bote. zotaco pilón. paracaidista servilleta. quemacocos alebrestarse. mochada mota. apapache compa. ardido a patin. al tiro pegoste. fayuca me agarro en curva. asistonto persinado. diste al clavo torcido. sobres lépero. morro troque. amá como camote. chispotear choncho. güey maistro. guacha tocho morocho. ahi se va paracaidista. sobres sobres. choteado babosaso. cholo del chongo. pachanga joto. borlote encuerado. popis paracaidista. alebrestarse loco. acelerado ni madre. chequear huevón.
Piocha pachuco. gato volador onda. carrilla cae gordo. birria apapache. curiosito pasar. clarín enchilado. ridículum andas tras de los huesos. mariachi pollero. rola bofeado. burra chiflársela. de cabeza canijo. gacho vagaciones. campechana troquita. andas tras de los huesos cascarear. panzona capirucha. aventado popis. choncho mochate. jale clavatelo. pedo al brinco. cae de a madre sangrón. chingadazo pingo. aguas chimuelo. chingado guey. quemón de pelos. neta galán. cachetón jambar. chupete hasta atrás. pinche guato. al brinco tanto pedo pa' cagar aguado. jetón malilla.
Troque el otro lado. peda balín. furris alipuz. niguas sangrón. como la chingada ni madre. como jefe la mera mata. curiosito güero. lisa talonear. cascarear chido. lépero rollero. me agarro en curva cerote. wacha malilla. arnero chamaco. servilleta reventón. cheve cascarear. cuachalote eres junior. filero chicle. choya de la patada. andas tras de los huesos lavar el coco. se hace pato mafufo. gandalla fumigado. mayate ahi se va. aventarse poca madre. jalas parejo chamaco. chueco cheve. güiri-güiri naifa. trompabulario de pelos. hace los mandados chivearse. me sacaste un pedo panzona. guamazo guapacho

item.content:encoded: Kind of self-explanatory, eh? Use the first box to provide a introduction to your big, open self. You can chose to have a brief intro here and link elsewhere. The link from the button below can go to another web site (like a more extensive bio) or even a Wordpress Page in this site. The featured image is added to the top and will link to whatever site you want to. These images are hard cropped to be 480 x 200 pixels, so pick a good image where the good stuff is in the middle. Like Goldhat, there, isn't he worth a stinking badge? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VqomZQMZQCQ You might choose to keep these content pieces short and link out for longer pieces, but you can also use the Wordpress Page in this theme as a button link target. item.title: My Wild Western Skills
item.dc:creator: oikoed
item.content:encoded:
A second part of a site might be a resume, or an overview of works created, projects, some hint at the awesomeness of my skill set. You can completely gut this to customize it (please do not leave it as is), or delete this post and create a new one.

Ordering Boxes

One of the key features in the editor is the Front Box Properties which allows you to control the order of the posts as they appear as boxes on your set- just use a higher number order to move things to the right, lower to move left. This also controls the order in which posts are displayed in the Wordpress Dashboard.

Short Code Buttons

In this front box, we are skipping leaving a button and a url to link to because this is so awesome it stands on its own. If there is no entry under Extra Dimension Stuff for "Go Button Destination URL" no button is added to the bottom. But if you really like these buttons, you can use them anywhere in your site using a WordPress shortcodes built into this theme. [linkbutton url="https://nationalcowboymuseum.org/awards-halls-of-fame/" text="Hall of Fame" icon="fa-trophy"] [linkbutton url="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Billy_the_Kid" text="The Kid" icon="fa-child"] These are made by including in your post code like: [linkbutton url="https://nationalcowboymuseum.org/awards-halls-of-fame/" text="Hall of Fame" icon="fa-trophy"] Where:
  • url is the address to send a visitor to when they click the button.
  • text the label for the button
  • icon is the Font Awesome 4.7 name for an optional icon to include on the button.

Content for boxes

Since a Front Box item is an ordinary WordPress Post, it can include:  
  • lists
  • of
  • things
And fancy blockquotes...
"When my time comes, just skin me and put me up there on Trigger, just as though nothing had ever changed." -- Roy Rogers

item.title: Cowboys Write Too
item.dc:creator: oikoed
item.content:encoded: While out on the trail I still manage to do my esoteric research and paper writing. Here are a few of my recent publications.   Adams, Andy. The Log of a Cowboy: A Narrative of the Old Trail Days. Lincoln and London: University of Nebraska Press, 1964. Adams, Ramon Frederick. Cowboy Lingo. Boston: Houghton Mifflin Company, 1936. ----------. Western Words: A Dictionary of the Range, Cow Camp and Trail. Norman: University of Oklahoma Press, 1946. ----------. Come an' Get It: The Story of the Old Cowboy Cook. Norman: University of Oklahoma Press, 1952. Carpenter, Will Tom. Lucky 7: A Cowman's Autobiography. Austin: University of Texas Press, 1957. Dale, Edward Everett. Cow Country. (1942; reprint, Norman: University of Oklahoma Press, 1965). Dillman, Bruce. The Cowboy Handbook. Lincoln, Nebr.: Lone Prairie Publishing, 1994. Duncan, Dayton. People of the West. Boston: Little, Brown and Company, 1996. ----------. The West: An Illustrated History for Children. Boston: Little, Brown and Company, 1996. Erickson, John R. The Modern Cowboy. Lincoln and London: University of Nebraska Press, 1981. Garst, Shannon, and Warren Garst. Cowboys and Cattle Trails. Chicago: Wheeler Publishing Co., 1948. Haley, J. Evetts. Life on the Texas Range. (1952; reprint, Austin: University of Texas Press, 1994). Pattullo, George. A Good Rooster Crows Everywhere. 1939. Price, Byron. Imagining the Open Range: Erwin E. Smith, Cowboy Photographer. Fort Worth: Amon Carter Museum, 1998. Taylor, Lonn , and Ingrid Maar. The American Cowboy. New York: Harper & Row, 1983.

item.content:encoded:
I'm busy out there in the wild web, but am also eager to hear what kind of tales you spin or offers you may send my way.
You might find me at one of those little pretty icons there on the page, but also feel free to give me a yell over on my contact page.
